
{
    Que -1: What is hooks....?
    Ans - Hooks were added to React in version 16.8.
    Hooks allow function components to have access to state and other React features. Because of this, class components are generally no longer needed.
    Hooks allow to manage state and lifecycle of componets
}

{
    Que - 2: Define useState hooks...?
    Ans  - The React useState Hook allows us to track state in a function component.
    State generally refers to data or properties that need to be tracking in an application.
    Available in react package;
}

{
    Que - 3 How to initialize state ..?
    Ans - We initialize our state by calling useState in our function component.
    useState accepts an initial state and returns two values:
    The current state.
    A function that updates the state.
}

{
    Que - 4 Syntax of useState ...?
    Ans - const[initialState, setInitialState] = useState("");
          const[varName, updateFunction] =useState("");
}

{
    Que - 5 Why do we use const even we are changing the state value...?
    Ans - The const keyword is used in JavaScript to declare variables that cannot be reassigned.
    We are not assigning any new value to state only updating state value;
    So the refernece is contant but we can change value not reference
}